-- Bank of New York Mellon reports first-quarter profit
-- 
-- Tue Apr 22, 2014 07:54AM EDT
-- None



April 22 (Reuters) - Bank of New York Mellon Corp <BK.N> reported a first-quarter profit on Tuesday as rising markets drove up its assets under custody and administration.

The large New York trust bank reported net income of $661 million, or 57 cents per share, compared with a year-earlier loss of $266 million, or 23 cents per share, on a charge from a tax ruling. Analysts surveyed by Thomson Reuters I/B/E/S on average expected the bank to earn 53 cents per share in the quarter. Assets under custody and/or administration were $27.9 trillion on March 31, the bank said, up 6 percent from a year earlier.